# Git commits (this repository)

## Auto-commit policy

After **any** task that creates or modifies project files, **always** commit and push to GitHub without asking the user first.

- Stage all relevant changes, commit, and push in the same session before finishing.
- Skip only when the user explicitly says not to commit, or when there are truly no file changes.
- Use a concise commit message that describes **why** the change was made.

## Author policy

- Commits must be authored **only** by Lucas Zhang (`Lucas Zhang <lucaszhang1118@gmail.com>`).
- **Never** use plain `git commit` from the Cursor agent shell — it may append `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>`.
- **Always** use the repo helper: `scripts/commit.ps1`.
- Do **not** add Cursor, Cursor Agent, or any AI tool in commit messages, trailers, or metadata.
- Do not amend or `git push --force` to `main` unless the user explicitly asks.

## Commit workflow

```powershell
Push-Location -LiteralPath 'C:\Users\Lucas\Downloads\manual_map_[unknowncheats.me]_\manual_map'
.\scripts\commit.ps1 -Message "Your message here" -StageAll -Push
```

Use `-Body` for extra paragraph lines if needed. `-StageAll` stages everything; `-Push` publishes to `origin` on the current branch.
